y Yash Pathak. It also has broadcast television shows with Bollywood celebrities in the main roles such as Sridevi in Malini Iyer, Karisma Kapoor in Karishma - The Miracles of Destiny, Raveena Tandon in Sahib Biwi Gulam and Hema Malini in Kamini Damini.[7] References[edit] ^ "Sahara One". Saharaone.in. 10 October 2004. Archived from the original on 23 July 2010. Retrieved 17 July 2010. ^ "Sahara One searches for success recipe | TelevisionPost.com". www.televisionpost.com. Archived from the original on 21 February 2015. ^ "India's Sahara Television Puts Their Trust In Tektronix". Embeddedstar.com. Retrieved 17 July 2010. ^ "Indian Television Dot Com". Indian Television Dot Com. ^ "Watch 'Woh Rehne Waali Mehlon Ki' and join Pari as she struggles for a decent way of life". indiantelevision.com. 22 April 2008. ^ "Chacha Chaudhary creator on Indian comics". Hindustan Times – Mahim Gupta. 2014. Archived from the original on 7 August 2014. ^ "Sahara One Bollywood Celebrity Shows". AFaqs – Prajjal Shah. 2004. External links[edit] Sahara One official website Sahara One Media and Entertainment Limited Sahara One Motion Pictures v t e Sahara One Shows Drama Kismat Connection... Sundeep Koachar Ke Saath Masakali Mythological Jai Jai Jai Bajrang Bali Other Masala Gupshup contentType 24 text/html; charset=UTF-8 url 44 https://en.wikipedia.org:443/wiki/Sahara_One responseCode 3 200 